- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper gives special consideration to soft or human-related factors in software engineering that are often not analysed with equal detail as more technical factors. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is another possible category as the paper is specifically focused on factors influencing productivity in software development. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may touch on programming language-related factors that influence productivity. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper may discuss the societal impact of productivity factors in software development.
